President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Arkansas due to severe storms, tornadoes, and straight-line winds that occurred on March 28, 2020. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Roland Jackson has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.